himself in the head.

252
00:22:30,075 --> 00:22:34,006
At first, I thought they
handed me the wrong dossier.

253
00:22:34,079 --> 00:22:37,515
I couldn't believe they
wanted this man dead.

254
00:22:37,583 --> 00:22:40,347
Third generation West Point,

255
00:22:40,419 --> 00:22:43,411
top of his class,
Korea, Airborne,

256
00:22:43,489 --> 00:22:45,889
about a thousand decorations,

257
00:22:45,958 --> 00:22:47,619
et cetera, et cetera.

258
00:22:50,262 --> 00:22:52,526
I'd heard his voice on the tape,

259
00:22:52,598 --> 00:22:55,032
and it really put
the hook in me,

260
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:58,092
but I couldn't connect
up that voice

261
00:22:58,170 --> 00:22:59,694
with this man.

262
00:23:05,844 --> 00:23:09,712
Like they said, he had
an impressive career,

263
00:23:09,782 --> 00:23:12,216
maybe too impressive.

264
00:23:12,284 --> 00:23:14,218
I mean perfect.

265
00:23:14,871 --> 00:23:18,751
He was being groomed for one of
the top slots in the corporation,

266
00:23:18,831 --> 00:23:21,671
General, Chief of
Staff, anything.

267
00:23:23,961 --> 00:23:28,051
In 1964, he returned from a tour
with advisory command in Vietnam

268
00:23:28,141 --> 00:23:30,181
and things started to slip.

269
00:23:30,511 --> 00:23:34,811
His report to the Joint Chiefs of Staff
and Lyndon Johnson was restricted.

270
00:23:37,061 --> 00:23:38,902
Seems they didn't dig
what he had to tell them.

271
00:23:40,691 --> 00:23:43,691
During the next few months, he
made three requests for transfer

272
00:23:43,781 --> 00:23:49,031
to Airborne training, Fort Benning,
Georgia, and was finally accepted.

273
00:23:51,741 --> 00:23:53,201
Airborne?

274
00:23:55,961 --> 00:23:57,711
He was 38 years old.

275
00:23:59,711 --> 00:24:01,881
Why the fuck would he do that?

276
00:24:04,211 --> 00:24:07,511
1966, joins Special Forces,

277
00:24:08,551 --> 00:24:10,011
returns Vietnam.

278
00:24:11,921 --> 00:24:13,961
-Hey, what's that?
-Arc light.

279
00:24:14,051 --> 00:24:16,971
-What's that?
-B-52 strike.

280
00:24:17,051 --> 00:24:18,841
Man.

281
00:24:18,931 --> 00:24:20,301
-What's that?
-Arc light.

282
00:24:20,391 --> 00:24:23,431
I hate that. Every time I hear
that, something terrible happens.

283
00:24:23,561 --> 00:24:25,521
Charlie, don't never see
them or hear them, man.

284
00:24:25,601 --> 00:24:27,851
-There they are.
-Concussion will suck the air

285
00:24:27,941 --> 00:24:29,271
out of your damn lungs.

286
00:24:29,861 --> 00:24:32,981
-Something terrible is gonna happen.
-Smoke!

287
00:24:33,071 --> 00:24:34,821
Secondary burning.

288
00:24:34,901 --> 00:24:36,781
Hueys over there. Lots of Hueys.

289
00:24:36,861 --> 00:24:37,901
Let's have a look, Chief.

290
00:24:41,621 --> 00:24:44,161
It was the air cav,
First of the Ninth.

291
00:24:44,701 --> 00:24:45,701
That's them.

292
00:24:45,791 --> 00:24:48,121
Our escorts to the mouth
of the Nung River.

293
00:24:48,421 --> 00:24:52,001
But they were supposed to be waiting
for us another 30 km ahead.

294
00:24:52,421 --> 00:24:56,841
Well, Airmobile, those boys
just couldn't stay put.

295
00:25:09,311 --> 00:25:12,481
Kid, come on. Get down. Come on.

296
00:25:23,661 --> 00:25:26,241
First of the Ninth was
an old cavalry division

297
00:25:26,331 --> 00:25:29,871
that had cashed in its horses for
choppers and gone tear-assing around Nam

298
00:25:29,961 --> 00:25:31,751
looking for the shit.

299
00:25:32,291 --> 00:25:36,131
They'd given Charlie a few
surprises in their time here.

300
00:25:37,011 --> 00:25:40,681
But what they were mopping up now,
hadn't even happened yet an hour ago.

301
00:25:42,141 --> 00:25:44,261
Just keep running by.
Run for television.

302
00:25:44,351 --> 00:25:46,761
Don't look at the camera. Just keep...
Go on! Keep going.

303
00:25:46,851 --> 00:25:48,431
This is for television.
Don't look at the camera.

304
00:25:48,521 --> 00:25:49,601
Don't look at the camera.

305
00:25:49,691 --> 00:25:51,891
Just go by like you're fighting.
Like you're fighting.

306
00:25:51,981 --> 00:25:54,651
Don't look at the camera. It's
for television. Just go through!

307
00:25:54,731 --> 00:25:57,281
Go through! Just go by!
Keep on going!

308
00:25:57,361 --> 00:26:01,201
Keep going. Don't look at the camera.
Go on. Keep going.

309
00:26:22,891 --> 00:26:24,801
Where can I find the CO?

310
00:26:24,931 --> 00:26:27,181
That's the Colonel coming down!

311
00:26:37,651 --> 00:26:39,691
The CO's on that chopper.

312
00:27:02,761 --> 00:27:06,141
Lieutenant, bomb that tree
line back about 100 yards!

313
00:27:06,351 --> 00:27:09,761
-Give me some room to breathe!
-Yes, sir!

314
00:27:14,731 --> 00:27:16,561
-Body cards!
-Sir?

315
00:27:16,651 --> 00:27:18,771
-Bring my body cards!
-Yes, sir!

316
00:27:22,901 --> 00:27:25,401
I'm the fourth tank commander.
I got five tanks broken down.

317
00:27:25,491 --> 00:27:28,451
We're all right with the tanks.
It's all right, Captain.

318
00:27:28,951 --> 00:27:29,991
Captain Willard!

319
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:33,871
I carry priority papers from
Com-Sec Intelligence, II Corps.

320
00:27:33,961 --> 00:27:37,631
I understand Nha Trang has briefed you
on the requirements of my mission.

321
00:27:37,711 --> 00:27:40,381
What mission? I haven't
heard from Nha Trang.

322
00:27:40,461 --> 00:27:43,211
Sir, your unit is supposed
to escort us into the Nung!

323
00:27:43,301 --> 00:27:45,221
-We'll see what we can do, but...
-Colonel.

324
00:27:45,301 --> 00:27:47,462
Just stay out of my way until
this is done, Captain.

325
00:27:53,311 --> 00:27:55,891
All right, let's see what we have.
Let's see what we have.

326
00:27:55,981 --> 00:28:00,021
A two of spades, three of
spades, four of diamonds,

327
00:28:01,111 --> 00:28:03,821
six of clubs, eight of spades.

328
00:28:04,991 --> 00:28:07,161
There isn't one worth a
jack in the whole bunch.

329
00:28:07,491 --> 00:28:08,991
Four of diamonds.

330
00:28:10,121 --> 00:28:13,911
-Hey, Captain, what's that?
-Death cards!

331
00:28:14,331 --> 00:28:17,081
-What?
-Death cards!

332
00:28:17,171 --> 00:28:19,831
-Death?
-It lets Charlie know who did this.

333
00:28:23,671 --> 00:28:26,091
-Cheer up, son.
-We will not hurt or harm you.

334
00:28:26,181 --> 00:28:28,801
-Fire in the hole!
-Fire in the hole!

335
00:28:31,181 --> 00:28:37,021
This is an area that is controlled by
the Viet Cong and North Vietnamese.

336
00:28:42,071 --> 00:28:44,151
We are here to help you.

337
00:28:47,401 --> 00:28:50,741
-We are here to extend a welcome hand...
-Come on.

338
00:28:50,821 --> 00:28:52,871
To those of you who would like...
Everybody in?

339
00:28:52,951 --> 00:28:56,541
To return to the arms of the
South Vietnamese government.

340
00:28:58,421 --> 00:28:59,671
Hurry up!

341
00:29:01,921 --> 00:29:03,251
Move it out!

342
00:29:03,341 --> 00:29:09,051
This is an area that is controlled by
the Viet Cong and North Vietnamese.

343
00:29:09,841 --> 00:29:11,391
Hey! What's this?

344
00:29:12,551 --> 00:29:13,891
What is this?

345
00:29:14,721 --> 00:29:16,971
This man's hurt pretty bad, sir.

346
00:29:17,061 --> 00:29:19,311
About the only thing that's
holding his guts in, sir,

347
00:29:19,391 --> 00:29:20,901
-is that pot lid.
-Yeah?

348
00:29:21,101 --> 00:29:22,611
What does he have to say?

349
00:29:23,321 --> 00:29:25,361
This soldier is dirty VC.

350
00:29:25,531 --> 00:29:28,821
He wants water. He can
drink paddy water.

351
00:29:30,031 --> 00:29:32,621
Get out of here! Give
me that canteen.

352
00:29:32,621 --> 00:29:35,581
-He's VC!
-Any man that's brave enough to...

353
00:29:35,661 --> 00:29:38,501
Get out of here! I'll
kick your fucking ass!

354
00:29:38,751 --> 00:29:40,001
He killed a lot of our people!

355
00:29:40,081 --> 00:29:42,921
Any man brave enough to fight
with his guts strapped on him

356
00:29:43,001 --> 00:29:44,841
can drink from my
canteen any day!

357
00:29:44,921 --> 00:29:48,711
Hey, Colonel, I think one of those
sailors is Lance Johnson, the surfer.

358
00:29:48,801 --> 00:29:51,591
-Where? Here? You sure?
-Down there.

359
00:29:53,101 --> 00:29:54,511
Yeah? Here.

360
00:29:55,101 --> 00:29:57,851
Repeat, we have a body count.
We have...

361
00:30:01,021 --> 00:30:04,861
What's your name, sailor?
-Gunner's Mate Third Class L. Johnson, sir!

362
00:30:04,941 --> 00:30:08,071
-Gunner's Mate Third Class...
-Wait. Lance Johnson, the surfer?

363
00:30:08,361 --> 00:30:11,701
-Yes, sir.
-Well, it's an honor to meet you, Lance.

364
00:30:11,781 --> 00:30:14,121
I've admired your nose
riding for years.

365
00:30:14,201 --> 00:30:17,161
I like your cutback, too. I think
you have the best cutback there is.

366
00:30:17,241 --> 00:30:19,951
-Thank you, sir.
-You can cut out the "sir" crap, Lance.

367
00:30:20,041 --> 00:30:22,041
I'm Bill Kilgore.
I'm a goofy foot.

368
00:30:22,121 --> 00:30:24,131
-This guy with you?
-Yeah.

369
00:30:24,381 --> 00:30:27,461
I want you to meet some guys.
This is Mike from San Diego.

370
00:30:27,551 --> 00:30:29,171
-Far out.
-Johnny from Malibu.

371
00:30:29,261 --> 00:30:31,381
-John, hi. Far out.
-Pretty solid surfers.

372
00:30:31,471 --> 00:30:33,261
None of us are anywhere
near your class, though.

373
00:30:33,341 --> 00:30:34,761
No way.

374
00:30:34,851 --> 00:30:38,601
We do a lot of surfing around here, Lance.
I like to finish operations early,

375
00:30:38,771 --> 00:30:41,811
fly down to Vung Tau
for the evening glass.

376
00:30:42,646 --> 00:30:44,326
-Been riding since you got here?
-No way.

377
00:30:44,351 --> 00:30:46,481
I haven't surfed
since I been here.

378
00:30:47,691 --> 00:30:50,781
Through Christ our Lord, from
whom all good things come.

379
00:30:50,861 --> 00:30:53,701
Through him in the unity
of the Holy Spirit,

380
00:30:53,781 --> 00:30:57,451
all glory and honor is yours,
Almighty Father. Amen.

381
00:30:57,531 --> 00:31:01,501
Let us pray with confidence to the
Father in the words our savior gave us.

382
00:31:02,041 --> 00:31:06,041
Our Father who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.

383
00:31:06,341 --> 00:31:08,751
Thy Kingdom come,
thy will be done

384
00:31:09,001 --> 00:31:10,961
on Earth as it is in heaven.

385
00:31:11,171 --> 00:31:13,171
Give us this day
our daily bread...

386
00:31:15,341 --> 00:31:18,101
as we forgive those who
trespass against us.

387
00:31:18,181 --> 00:31:21,641
Lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

388
00:31:31,651 --> 00:31:34,701
Kilgore had had a pretty
good day for himself.

389
00:31:34,861 --> 00:31:37,111
They choppered in the
T-bones and the beer

390
00:31:37,201 --> 00:31:39,621
and turned the LZ
into a beach party.

391
00:31:40,831 --> 00:31:43,541
The more they tried to
make it just like home,

392
00:31:43,621 --> 00:31:46,171
the more they made
everybody miss it.

393
00:31:46,421 --> 00:31:49,631
Make my meat rare,
rare but not cold!

394
00:31:55,431 --> 00:31:58,261
Well, he wasn't a bad
officer, I guess.

395
00:31:59,221 --> 00:32:02,601
He loved his boys and
you felt safe with him.

396
00:32:02,891 --> 00:32:06,271
He was one of those guys that had
that weird light around him.

397
00:32:06,351 --> 00:32:09,691
You just knew he wasn't gonna
get so much as a scratch here.

398
00:32:09,771 --> 00:32:13,611
What happened to your mission, Captain?
Nha Trang forget all about you?

399
00:32:22,081 --> 00:32:23,331
Airborne.

400
00:32:25,081 --> 00:32:28,371
Sir, two places we can
get into the river...

401
00:32:28,541 --> 00:32:31,171
Yeah... Here and here.

402
00:32:31,251 --> 00:32:33,711
It's a pretty wide delta, but
these are the only two spots

403
00:32:33,801 --> 00:32:35,051
I'm really sure of.

404
00:32:36,381 --> 00:32:39,301
Well, that village you're pointing
at is kind of hairy, Willard.

405
00:32:39,801 --> 00:32:42,051
-What do you mean "hairy," sir?
-It's hairy,

406
00:32:42,141 --> 00:32:43,891
got some pretty heavy ordnance.

407
00:32:43,971 --> 00:32:46,771
I lost a few recon ships
in there now and again.

408
00:32:47,191 --> 00:32:49,311
What's the name of that goddamn village?
Vin Drin...

409
00:32:49,691 --> 00:32:51,561
-Dop.
-Dop or Lop?

410
00:32:52,321 --> 00:32:54,781
Damn gook names all
sound the same.

411
00:32:56,451 --> 00:32:59,491
Mike, you know anything about
this point at Vin Drin Dop?

412
00:32:59,871 --> 00:33:01,371
That's a fantastic peak.

413
00:33:02,161 --> 00:33:04,081
-Peak?
-About six foot.

414
00:33:04,161 --> 00:33:07,371
Yeah, it's an outstanding peak. It's
got both the long right and left slide

415
00:33:07,461 --> 00:33:09,581
with a bowl section.
It's unbelievable.

416
00:33:09,671 --> 00:33:11,751
It's just tube city.

417
00:33:15,421 --> 00:33:17,551
Well, why didn't you tell me that before?
A good peak.

418
00:33:17,631 --> 00:33:20,181
There aren't any good peaks
in this whole shitty country.

419
00:33:20,261 --> 00:33:22,221
It's all goddamn beach break.

420
00:33:22,301 --> 00:33:24,311
It's really hairy in there, sir.
That's where we lost McDonald.

421
00:33:24,391 --> 00:33:25,791
They shot the hell
out of us there.

422
00:33:26,601 --> 00:33:28,481
That's Charlie's point.

423
00:33:29,851 --> 00:33:32,401
Sir, we can go in there
tomorrow at dawn.

424
00:33:32,481 --> 00:33:34,561
There's always a good offshore
breeze in the morning.

425
00:33:34,821 --> 00:33:36,651
We may not be able
to get the boat in.

426
00:33:36,861 --> 00:33:39,201
The draft at the mouth of that
river may be too shallow.

427
00:33:40,596 --> 00:33:43,636
We'll pick your boat up and put it down
like a baby, right where you want it.

428
00:33:43,661 --> 00:33:46,831
This is the First of the Ninth
air cav, son. Airmobile.

429
00:33:48,065 --> 00:33:50,306
I can take that point and hold
it just as long as I like.

430
00:33:50,331 --> 00:33:53,501
And you can get any place up that
river that suits you, young Captain.

431
00:33:53,961 --> 00:33:55,711
Hell, a six-foot peak.

432
00:33:57,801 --> 00:33:59,642
All right, take a gunship
back to the division.

433
00:33:59,721 --> 00:34:01,801
Lance, go with Mike and let
him pick out a board for you,

434
00:34:01,891 --> 00:34:03,641
and bring me my Yater
Spoon, the 8'6".

435
00:34:03,721 --> 00:34:06,221
-I don't know, sir, it's...
-What is it, soldier?

436
00:34:06,471 --> 00:34:09,141
Well, I mean, it's pretty hairy in there.
It's Charlie's point.

437
00:34:09,231 --> 00:34:11,231
Charlie don't surf!

438
00:34:35,041 --> 00:34:38,211
Hey, Jesus, Clean, you ain't
gonna believe this. Look.

439
00:34:39,671 --> 00:34:42,721
Hey, man! They're
picking up the boat!

440
00:34:45,551 --> 00:34:49,391
-How are you feeling, Jimmy?
-Like a mean motherfucker, sir!

441
00:34:51,641 --> 00:34:53,521
All right, son, let her rip.

442
00:34:53,941 --> 00:34:55,311
Let's go!

443
00:36:18,441 --> 00:36:22,231
I never have gotten used to a light
board, and I can't get used to one.

444
00:36:22,321 --> 00:36:24,941
-I'm used to a heavy board.
-I know, it's a real drag.

445
00:36:25,741 --> 00:36:28,491
-You prefer a heavy or a light board?
-Heavier.

446
00:36:28,571 --> 00:36:29,781
-Really?
-Yeah!

447
00:36:29,871 --> 00:36:31,911
I thought all the young
guys like lighter boards.

448
00:36:31,991 --> 00:36:34,201
You can't ride the
nose on those things.

449
00:36:34,291 --> 00:36:37,621
Big Duke Six, this is Eagle Thrust Seven.
We've got it spotted.

450
00:36:37,711 --> 00:36:41,091
Big Duke Six to Eagle Thrust,
put on heading 2-7-0.

451
00:36:41,171 --> 00:36:42,801
Assume attack formation.

452
00:36:43,001 --> 00:36:45,591
That's a roger, Big Duke.
Okay, we're going in.

453
00:36:45,671 --> 00:36:49,591
Lance, we'll come in low
out of the rising sun,

454
00:36:49,681 --> 00:36:51,721
and about a mile out,
we'll put on the music.

455
00:36:52,181 --> 00:36:54,521
-Music?
-Yeah, I use Wagner.

456
00:36:54,721 --> 00:36:58,101
Scares the hell out of the slopes.
My boys love it.

457
00:36:58,851 --> 00:37:00,811
Hey, they're gonna play music!

458
00:37:07,781 --> 00:37:10,361
How come all you guys
sit on your helmet?

459
00:37:11,571 --> 00:37:14,121
So we don't get our
balls blown off.

460
00:37:25,381 --> 00:37:30,221
Big Duke Six to Eagle Thrust, put
on psy war op, make it loud.

461
00:37:30,721 --> 00:37:34,101
This is a Romeo Foxtrot.
Shall we dance?

462
00:37:38,521 --> 00:37:40,191
-Jimmy!
-Yes, sir!

463
00:40:19,851 --> 00:40:21,011
Run, Charlie!

464
00:40:40,621 --> 00:40:42,831
We got some... There's
more and more down there.

465
00:40:42,911 --> 00:40:45,581
Look out, automatic .50-cal!
.50-cal in the open!

466
00:40:46,081 --> 00:40:49,831
I've spotted a large weapon down below.
We're gonna go down and check it out.

467
00:40:49,921 --> 00:40:52,091
All right, this is Fox Five.
We're going in.

468
00:41:02,891 --> 00:41:06,221
-All right. What a shot.
-Outstanding, Red Team. Outstanding.

469
00:41:06,311 --> 00:41:07,771
Get you a case of beer for that.

470
00:41:29,421 --> 00:41:31,921
6-4-1-0, we're over the
village right now.

471
00:41:32,001 --> 00:41:33,881
I think I see a vehicle
down in the courtyard.

472
00:41:33,961 --> 00:41:37,131
-I'm gonna check it out.
-Well done, hawks. Well done.

473
00:41:37,341 --> 00:41:40,471
I want some 20 Mike-Mike Vulcan
right along those tree lines.

474
00:41:40,721 --> 00:41:42,391
Ripple the shit out of them.

475
00:41:42,681 --> 00:41:44,891
Got a vehicle on the bridge,
.50 caliber on board.

476
00:41:44,971 --> 00:41:47,641
He's moving across to
resupply the weapon.

477
00:41:48,101 --> 00:41:51,521
Big Duke Six, clear the area.
I'm coming down myself.

478
00:41:51,771 --> 00:41:53,061
Don't these people ever give up?

479
00:41:57,151 --> 00:41:58,571
Nice shot, Bill.

480
00:42:00,321 --> 00:42:02,031
-Shit!
-All right, all right!

481
00:42:02,161 --> 00:42:07,411
-It's just a flare!
-It's a flare! Gotta get out of here!

482
00:42:07,501 --> 00:42:09,451
Un-ass that shit.
