01:55:46,031 --> 01:55:49,291
Chef, Chef, on the .60.

1399
01:56:11,981 --> 01:56:13,231
Fuck me.

1400
01:56:50,971 --> 01:56:52,141
Lance.

1401
01:57:22,011 --> 01:57:25,841
Cover the Captain. Lance,
cover the Captain.

1402
01:57:43,821 --> 01:57:45,531
They're French. They're French.

1403
01:57:47,071 --> 01:57:50,161
Chef, pick up that weapon!
Pick it up! Pick it up!

1404
01:57:50,371 --> 01:57:52,201
Stand fast! Captain...

1405
01:58:27,611 --> 01:58:29,741
All right, you men, put
down your weapons.

1406
01:59:18,791 --> 01:59:20,161
New Orleans.

1407
01:59:24,881 --> 01:59:26,711
We lost one of our men.

1408
01:59:30,431 --> 01:59:35,431
We French always pay respects
to the dead of our allies.

1409
01:59:37,141 --> 01:59:38,931
You are all welcome.

1410
01:59:41,691 --> 01:59:43,811
My name is Hubert de Marais.

1411
01:59:45,321 --> 01:59:47,571
This is my family's plantation.

1412
01:59:48,491 --> 01:59:50,651
It has been such for 70 years.

1413
01:59:52,661 --> 01:59:55,411
And it will be such
until we are all dead.

1414
02:02:07,541 --> 02:02:13,001
Captain, accept the flag of Tyrone
Miller on behalf of a grateful nation.

1415
02:02:33,361 --> 02:02:37,901
This food is really wonderful, isn't it?
The wine, the sauces. I can't believe it.

1416
02:02:37,991 --> 02:02:39,951
Can I speak with the chef?

1417
02:02:40,161 --> 02:02:42,121
The chef speaks only Vietnamese.

1418
02:02:42,451 --> 02:02:46,411
No kidding. He cooks like this
and he can't even speak French?

1419
02:02:46,501 --> 02:02:49,161
Hey, Lance, the chef's a slope.

1420
02:02:51,501 --> 02:02:53,001
Hey, Lance.

1421
02:03:21,781 --> 02:03:23,411
This is Baudelaire.

1422
02:03:23,491 --> 02:03:26,581
It's a very cruel poem for
children, but they need it,

1423
02:03:26,661 --> 02:03:29,331
because life sometimes
is very cruel.

1424
02:03:31,171 --> 02:03:32,791
As you can see...

1425
02:03:36,131 --> 02:03:39,971
-Attacks repelled by the family.
-Just for this war.

1426
02:03:40,471 --> 02:03:43,011
Viet Cong, 58.

1427
02:03:43,221 --> 02:03:45,051
North Vietnamese, 12.

1428
02:03:45,761 --> 02:03:47,641
South Vietnamese, 11.

1429
02:03:48,561 --> 02:03:50,351
Americans, six.

1430
02:03:51,891 --> 02:03:54,731
Yes, well, they were
perhaps mistakes.

1431
02:04:15,921 --> 02:04:18,841
May I present Captain Willard?
He's of a paratroop regiment.

1432
02:04:19,421 --> 02:04:21,591
-Madame Sarrault.
-Captain.

1433
02:04:49,291 --> 02:04:52,201
I'm sorry, Captain. Was just
a little story about Paris

1434
02:04:52,291 --> 02:04:53,541
and people starving
during the war.

1435
02:04:53,621 --> 02:04:55,711
They are around the table
and there was a silence.

1436
02:04:55,791 --> 02:04:58,341
Somebody says, "An
angel is passing by."

1437
02:04:58,671 --> 02:05:01,341
So somebody said,
"Let's eat it."

1438
02:05:09,471 --> 02:05:12,811
How long can you
possibly stay here?

1439
02:05:13,231 --> 02:05:14,771
We stay forever.

1440
02:05:15,521 --> 02:05:17,271
No, no, I mean,

1441
02:05:18,941 --> 02:05:20,981
when will you go
back home to France?

1442
02:05:24,201 --> 02:05:25,951
I mean, this is our
home, Captain.

1443
02:05:26,491 --> 02:05:28,161
-Sooner or later you're gonna...
-No!

1444
02:05:30,331 --> 02:05:34,001
You don't understand our mentality,
the French Officer mentality.

1445
02:05:34,961 --> 02:05:37,251
At first, we lose in
Second World War.

1446
02:05:37,331 --> 02:05:40,131
I don't say that you
Americans win, but we lose.

1447
02:05:42,631 --> 02:05:45,511
In Dien Bien Phu, we lose.
In Nigeria, we lose.

1448
02:05:45,591 --> 02:05:47,381
In Indochina, we lose.

1449
02:05:48,051 --> 02:05:50,511
But here, we don't lose.

1450
02:05:51,181 --> 02:05:56,271
This piece of earth, we keep it!
We will never lose that, never!

1451
02:06:01,771 --> 02:06:03,531
The Americans,

1452
02:06:06,401 --> 02:06:09,361
in 1945, yes,

1453
02:06:09,781 --> 02:06:11,871
after the Japanese War,

1454
02:06:12,701 --> 02:06:15,121
your President Roosevelt
didn't want the French people

1455
02:06:15,201 --> 02:06:17,291
to stay in Indochina.

1456
02:06:19,211 --> 02:06:22,001
So, you Americans

1457
02:06:22,091 --> 02:06:24,051
invent the Viet Minh.

1458
02:06:26,051 --> 02:06:27,881
-What's he mean?
-Yeah, that's true.

1459
02:06:28,091 --> 02:06:30,551
The Viet Cong were invented
by the Americans, sir.

1460
02:06:31,891 --> 02:06:33,101
The Americans?

1461
02:06:33,721 --> 02:06:38,061
Now you take the French place,
and the Viet Minh fight you,

1462
02:06:38,641 --> 02:06:40,521
and what can you do?

1463
02:06:40,611 --> 02:06:43,061
Nothing. Absolutely nothing.

1464
02:06:43,231 --> 02:06:46,321
The Vietnamese are very intelligent.
You never know what they think.

1465
02:06:46,741 --> 02:06:48,741
The Russians want to help them.

1466
02:06:49,111 --> 02:06:51,741
"Come and give us some money.
We are all communists."

1467
02:06:52,071 --> 02:06:54,371
"Chinese, give us guns.
We are all brothers."

1468
02:06:54,451 --> 02:06:55,911
They hate the Chinese.

1469
02:06:56,791 --> 02:07:00,961
Maybe they hate Americans less
than the Russians and the Chinese.

1470
02:07:01,146 --> 02:07:03,106
I mean, if tomorrow the
Vietnamese are communists,

1471
02:07:03,131 --> 02:07:05,381
they will be
Vietnamese communists.

1472
02:07:06,011 --> 02:07:08,721
And this is something that you
never understood, you Americans.

1473
02:07:09,431 --> 02:07:11,721
I don't know. Maybe
in the future

1474
02:07:11,801 --> 02:07:14,261
we can make something
with the Viet Minh.

1475
02:07:14,511 --> 02:07:16,101
Don't you understand?

1476
02:07:16,431 --> 02:07:19,141
The VC say, "Go away! Go away!"

1477
02:07:19,271 --> 02:07:21,981
That's finished for all the
white people in Indochina.

1478
02:07:22,061 --> 02:07:25,231
If you're French, American,
that's all the same.

1479
02:07:25,441 --> 02:07:29,111
Go! They want to forget you.
Look at them.

1480
02:07:31,241 --> 02:07:33,991
Look, this is the truth. An egg.

1481
02:07:37,161 --> 02:07:38,701
The white left.

1482
02:07:40,211 --> 02:07:42,081
The yellow stay.

1483
02:07:50,131 --> 02:07:51,301
When I was in Saigon,

1484
02:07:51,381 --> 02:07:55,141
I spoke to an American politician
and he explained it very well.

1485
02:07:55,221 --> 02:07:58,851
He said, "Look, yesterday
it was Korea",

1486
02:07:58,931 --> 02:08:04,811
"today, Vietnam, tomorrow, Thailand, the
Philippines, and then maybe Europe."

1487
02:08:07,481 --> 02:08:08,611
Why not Europe?

1488
02:08:08,691 --> 02:08:11,071
Look what happened in
Czechoslovakia recently!

1489
02:08:11,241 --> 02:08:12,861
And even before the
Second World War,

1490
02:08:12,951 --> 02:08:15,031
the Americans knew exactly
what was going on.

1491
02:08:15,121 --> 02:08:17,531
They don't want that
shit to take over!

1492
02:08:20,451 --> 02:08:24,961
-All you white people are shit.
-They are fighting. Fighting for freedom.

1493
02:08:25,041 --> 02:08:27,171
Freedom? Bullshit.

1494
02:08:27,551 --> 02:08:30,261
French bullshit.
American bullshit.

1495
02:08:30,721 --> 02:08:32,421
Dien Bien Phu is a trap.

1496
02:08:33,261 --> 02:08:36,341
All soldiers know they
are already dead.

1497
02:08:38,391 --> 02:08:40,311
You know anything
about Dien Bien Phu?

1498
02:08:43,441 --> 02:08:47,401
-Yeah, I know.
-No, you don't, not really.

1499
02:08:47,481 --> 02:08:50,481
Dien Bien Phu was an error, you know?
A military mistake.

1500
02:08:50,611 --> 02:08:54,281
A mistake? A voluntary mistake!
Voluntary!

1501
02:08:56,991 --> 02:09:00,951
All the soldiers knew. We
knew we would be dead.

1502
02:09:01,701 --> 02:09:03,461
Generals and colonels
believe it's impossible

1503
02:09:03,541 --> 02:09:07,831
for the Viets to get a cannon up
there in the mountains, but they do.

1504
02:09:08,591 --> 02:09:11,381
Then they wait for
the rain to come.

1505
02:09:12,551 --> 02:09:16,591
When it comes, no
airplane can fly there.

1506
02:09:16,801 --> 02:09:22,431
And our paratroopers jump at 90 meters. I
mean, you know, 90 meters, 70 meters...

1507
02:09:22,521 --> 02:09:25,691
I mean, that's crazy. No army
in the world can do that.

1508
02:09:26,271 --> 02:09:29,731
And they only do that to be
dead with their friends.

1509
02:09:31,731 --> 02:09:33,071
No, no!

1510
02:09:36,241 --> 02:09:38,411
The French army was sacrificed,

1511
02:09:38,621 --> 02:09:41,331
sacrificed by the
politicians safe at home.

1512
02:09:41,411 --> 02:09:44,132
They put the army in an impossible
situation where they couldn't win.

1513
02:09:45,331 --> 02:09:48,831
The students are marching in
Paris, protesting, demonstrating.

1514
02:09:48,921 --> 02:09:51,041
They stab the
soldiers in the back.

1515
02:09:51,171 --> 02:09:55,051
The soldier would open the
grenade, it wouldn't work.

1516
02:09:55,341 --> 02:09:57,131
A piece of paper would fall.

1517
02:09:59,511 --> 02:10:02,761
Union of French Women.
"We are for the Viets."

1518
02:10:03,061 --> 02:10:04,311
Traitors.

1519
02:10:04,771 --> 02:10:06,891
Communist traitors at home.

1520
02:10:08,311 --> 02:10:09,851
Dien Bien Phu...

1521
02:10:10,231 --> 02:10:12,771
Okay, the French is shit.

1522
02:10:14,901 --> 02:10:17,201
No one cares. No one wants to.

1523
02:10:19,821 --> 02:10:23,791
Why don't you Americans learn from us?
From our mistakes?

1524
02:10:24,121 --> 02:10:26,161
Mon dieu, with your army,
your strength, your power,

1525
02:10:26,211 --> 02:10:27,411
you can win if you want to.

1526
02:10:30,461 --> 02:10:31,881
You can win.

1527
02:10:35,091 --> 02:10:38,301
You know, I'm sure we can
make something there.

1528
02:10:39,051 --> 02:10:40,641
I'm sure about it, you know?

1529
02:10:41,181 --> 02:10:43,721
I never do something wrong
to the people here.

1530
02:10:44,311 --> 02:10:47,731
I'm sorry, you know, but the communists
at home have never been traitors.

1531
02:11:21,681 --> 02:11:25,011
Excuse me. I have to go.
Captain, good night.

1532
02:11:25,351 --> 02:11:27,931
-I was a socialist, you know?
-I know we can stay.

1533
02:11:28,021 --> 02:11:32,021
I know that we can stay.
We can stay.

1534
02:11:34,941 --> 02:11:38,321
You know, we always
help the people.

1535
02:11:38,401 --> 02:11:40,111
We work with the people.

1536
02:11:56,671 --> 02:12:00,801
See, Captain, when
my grandfather

1537
02:12:02,261 --> 02:12:04,511
and my uncles and
father came here,

1538
02:12:07,101 --> 02:12:09,681
there was nothing. Nothing.

1539
02:12:11,061 --> 02:12:13,231
The Vietnamese were nothing.

1540
02:12:15,151 --> 02:12:18,901
So, we worked hard, very hard.

1541
02:12:19,071 --> 02:12:23,861
We brought the rubber from
Brazil and then planted it here.

1542
02:12:24,781 --> 02:12:28,081
We took the Vietnamese,
work with them,

1543
02:12:28,491 --> 02:12:29,831
make something.

1544
02:12:30,581 --> 02:12:32,581
Something out of nothing.

1545
02:12:34,171 --> 02:12:37,841
So when you ask me why we
want to stay here, Captain,

1546
02:12:39,421 --> 02:12:41,841
we want to stay here
because it's ours.

1547
02:12:41,921 --> 02:12:43,381
It belongs to us.

1548
02:12:44,091 --> 02:12:45,761
It keeps our family together.

1549
02:12:47,511 --> 02:12:49,511
I mean, we fight for that.

1550
02:12:51,431 --> 02:12:53,231
While you Americans,

1551
02:12:54,141 --> 02:12:59,021
you are fighting for the
biggest nothing in history.

1552
02:13:06,991 --> 02:13:08,741
I'm sorry, Captain.

1553
02:13:09,241 --> 02:13:13,961
I will see if your men need
any help to repair your boat

1554
02:13:14,251 --> 02:13:17,631
so that you can go
on with your war.

1555
02:13:52,791 --> 02:13:55,461
I apologize for my
family, Captain.

1556
02:13:57,501 --> 02:13:59,631
We have all lost much here.

1557
02:14:01,171 --> 02:14:04,261
Hubert, his wife and two sons.

1558
02:14:08,681 --> 02:14:10,851
And I have lost a husband.

1559
02:14:16,771 --> 02:14:20,561
-I understand.
-You are tired of the war.

1560
02:14:22,651 --> 02:14:24,781
I can see on your face.

1561
02:14:27,401 --> 02:14:31,531
It was the same in the eyes
of the soldiers of our war.

1562
02:14:32,741 --> 02:14:33,791
We call them...

1563
02:14:36,911 --> 02:14:38,711
"The lost soldiers."

1564
02:14:43,591 --> 02:14:46,131
If you like, we can
have some cognac.

1565
02:14:50,891 --> 02:14:52,141
No.

1566
02:14:52,931 --> 02:14:55,891
I'll see about my men and...

1567
02:15:03,691 --> 02:15:06,281
The war will be still
here tomorrow.

1568
02:15:17,041 --> 02:15:19,081
Yeah, I guess you're right.

1569
02:15:27,091 --> 02:15:29,761
I noticed you had
no wine at dinner.

1570
02:15:31,011 --> 02:15:33,681
No, I don't drink wine.

1571
02:15:37,101 --> 02:15:41,601
I do like cognac, but I don't
want any now, thank you.

1572
02:15:45,231 --> 02:15:47,981
Well, then I must drink alone.

1573
02:15:58,291 --> 02:16:01,661
Will you go back, after
the war, to America?

1574
02:16:05,631 --> 02:16:08,631
-No.
-Then you're like us.

1575
02:16:08,881 --> 02:16:10,551
Your home is here.

1576
02:16:28,151 --> 02:16:32,071
Do you know why you can never
step into the same river twice?

1577
02:16:34,321 --> 02:16:37,491
Yeah, 'cause it's always moving.

1578
02:16:38,911 --> 02:16:42,041
I used to prepare a
pipe for my husband.

1579
02:16:49,341 --> 02:16:53,631
It was the morphine he took for the
wounds he suffered in his heart.

1580
02:16:57,301 --> 02:17:00,931
He would rage and he would
cry, my lost soldier.

1581
02:17:04,691 --> 02:17:06,351
And I said to him,

1582
02:17:07,111 --> 02:17:10,481
"There are two of
you, don't you see?"

1583
02:17:11,571 --> 02:17:15,201
"One that kills and
one that loves."

1584
02:17:17,321 --> 02:17:18,991
And he said to me,

1585
02:17:19,871 --> 02:17:23,501
"I don't know whether I
am an animal or a god."

1586
02:17:26,961 --> 02:17:28,581
But you are both.

1587
02:18:10,461 --> 02:18:12,211
You want more?

1588
02:18:17,931 --> 02:18:21,761
All that matters is
that you are alive.

1589
02:18:23,431 --> 02:18:25,351
You are alive, Captain.

1590
02:18:29,651 --> 02:18:31,271
That's the truth.

1591
02:19:45,181 --> 02:19:48,681
There are two of
you, don't you see?

1592
02:19:50,021 --> 02:19:54,191
One that kills and
one that loves.

1593
02:20:23,551 --> 02:20:26,101
Can't see nothing.
We're stopping.

1594
02:20:26,601 --> 02:20:28,971
You're not authorized to
stop this boat, Chief.

1595
02:20:29,061 --> 02:20:31,891
I said I can't see a thing, Captain.
I'm stopping this boat.

1596
02:20:32,641 --> 02:20:34,231
I ain't risking no more lives.

1597
02:20:34,311 --> 02:20:37,231
I'm in command here, God damn it.
You'll do what I say.

1598
02:20:39,401 --> 02:20:41,571
You see anything, Chef?

1599
02:20:43,571 --> 02:20:45,911
Why don't they
fucking attack, man?

1600
02:21:05,141 --> 02:21:07,261
Watch it over here, Chief.

1601
02:21:08,391 --> 02:21:10,061
Got a stump.

1602
02:21:11,481 --> 02:21:12,851
Lance, on the .50s.

1603
02:21:14,641 --> 02:21:16,441
He was close.

1604
02:21:18,481 --> 02:21:20,151
He was real close.

1605
02:21:22,441 --> 02:21:27,321
I couldn't see him yet, but I could feel him,
as if the boat were being sucked upriver

1606
02:21:27,411 --> 02:21:30,281
and the water was flowing
back into the jungle.

1607
02:21:32,831 --> 02:21:35,251
Whatever was going to happen,

1608
02:21:35,331 --> 02:21:39,291
it wasn't gonna be the way they
called it back in Nha Trang.

1609
02:21:43,971 --> 02:21:45,221
Arrows!

1610
02:21:45,301 --> 02:21:46,431
Fire!

1611
02:21:48,641 --> 02:21:49,891
Chef, open up! Fire!

1612
02:21:55,021 --> 02:21:56,981
Lance, fire!

1613
02:22:04,821 --> 02:22:08,111
Chef! Chef, it's okay.
Quit firing.

1614
02:22:08,621 --> 02:22:10,201
They're just little toy arrows.

1615
02:22:10,491 --> 02:22:12,411
Cut it out! Quiet!

1616
02:22:12,661 --> 02:22:14,911
Chief, tell them to
hold their fire!

1617
02:22:15,331 --> 02:22:17,691
They're just little sticks.
They're just trying to scare us.

1618
02:22:18,081 --> 02:22:19,421
Quiet!

1619
02:22:20,461 --> 02:22:23,251
You got us in this mess, and
now you can't get us out

1620
02:22:23,341 --> 02:22:25,661
because you don't know where
the hell you're going, do you?

1621
02:22:25,841 --> 02:22:27,011
Do you?

1622
02:22:28,011 --> 02:22:30,891
You son of a bitch! You bastard!

1623
02:22:32,511 --> 02:22:34,851
-Lance, get the wheel!
-Fire!

1624
02:22:35,521 --> 02:22:39,061
You savages! Come and get
it, you son of a bitches!

1625
02:22:59,541 --> 02:23:01,211
A spear.

1626
02:24:20,661 --> 02:24:23,501
My mission is to make
it up into Cambodia.

1627
02:24:24,131 --> 02:24:26,591
There's a Green Beret colonel
up there who's gone insane

1628
02:24:26,671 --> 02:24:28,551
and I'm supposed to kill him.

1629
02:24:29,971 --> 02:24:32,631
That's fucking typical! Shit!

1630
02:24:33,011 --> 02:24:34,971
Fucking Vietnam mission!

1631
02:24:35,301 --> 02:24:39,061
I'm short and we gotta go up there
so you can kill one of our own guys?

1632
02:24:39,141 --> 02:24:42,981
That's fucking great! That's
just fucking great, man.

1633
02:24:43,731 --> 02:24:46,611
Shit! That's fucking crazy.

1634
02:24:47,191 --> 02:24:50,151
I mean, I thought you were
going in to blow up a bridge

1635
02:24:50,281 --> 02:24:53,151
or some fucking rail road
tracks or something.

1636
02:24:54,161 --> 02:24:56,201
-Sorry.
-No, no, wait, wait.

1637
02:24:56,281 --> 02:24:59,581
We'll go together on the boat.
We'll go with you.

1638
02:24:59,661 --> 02:25:03,331
We'll go up there, but on the boat.
